articles.description: BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) — Louisiana Legislature votes to make abortion pills controlled dangerous substances under first-of-its-kind measure.
articles.title: Louisiana Legislature votes to make abortion pills controlled dangerous substances under first-of-its-kind measure

articles.author: TARA COPP and MATTHEW LEE
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — The United States is expected to announce an additional $275 million in military aid for Ukraine on Friday as Kyiv struggles to hold off advances by Russian troops in the Kharkiv region, two U.S.
articles.title: US will announce $275 million more in artillery and ammunition for Ukraine, officials say

articles.author: JON GAMBRELL
articles.description: DUBAI, United Arab Emirates (AP) — Iran interred President Ebrahim Raisi at the nation's holiest Shiite shrine Thursday, days after he was killed in a helicopter crash that added to the woes of a country already beset by international sanctions, internal unrest and tensions abroad.
articles.title: Iran inters its late president at holiest Shiite site in nation after fatal helicopter crash

articles.author: JOSEPH KRAUSS
articles.description: JERUSALEM (AP) — Diminished but not deterred, Hamas is still putting up a fight after seven brutal months of war with Israel, regrouping in some of the hardest-hit areas in northern Gaza and resuming rocket attacks into nearby Israeli communities.
articles.title: How does this end? With Hamas holding firm and fighting back in Gaza, Israel faces only bad options

articles.author: ALANNA DURKIN RICHER and WYATTE GRANTHAM-PHILIPS
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — The Justice Department filed a sweeping antitrust lawsuit against Ticketmaster and parent company Live Nation Entertainment on Thursday, accusing them of running an illegal monopoly over live events in America — squelching competition and driving up prices for fans.
articles.title: Justice Department says illegal monopoly by Ticketmaster and Live Nation drives up prices for fans

articles.author: STEPHEN GROVES and REBECCA SANTANA
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Senate Democrats are trying for a second time to push ahead with a bill to clamp down the number of migrants allowed to claim asylum at the U.S.-Mexico border as Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer sought on Thursday to underscore Republican resistance to the proposal.
articles.title: Senate holds a test vote on border bill as Democrats seek to underscore Republican resistance

articles.author: MATT O'BRIEN and BARBARA ORTUTAY
articles.description: President Joe Biden's administration is pushing the tech industry and financial institutions to shut down a growing market of abusive sexual images made with artificial intelligence technology.New generative AI tools have made it easy to transform someone's likeness into a sexually explicit AI deepfake and share those realistic images across chatrooms or social media.
articles.title: White House pushes tech industry to shut down market for sexually abusive AI deepfakes

articles.author: JILL LAWLESS
articles.description: LONDON (AP) — Britain’s political party leaders crisscrossed the country on Thursday, kicking off a six-week election campaign in which Prime Minister Rishi Sunak's Conservative Party is trying to overturn a widespread sense that it will be ousted from power.
articles.title: UK politicians kick off a 6-week election campaign with incumbent Sunak playing the underdog

articles.author: ANNIE MA
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — House Republicans have summoned the leaders of Northwestern University and Rutgers University to testify about concessions they gave to pro-Palestinian protesters to end demonstrations on their campus.
articles.title: Leaders of Northwestern, UCLA and Rutgers to testify before Congress on campus protests

articles.author: MICHELLE L. PRICE and JILL COLVIN
articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — Former President Donald Trump will campaign in one of the most Democratic counties in the nation Thursday, holding a rally in the South Bronx to woo minority voters days before a Manhattan jury will begin deliberations on whether to convict him of felony charges in his criminal hush money trial.
articles.title: Trump is holding a rally in the South Bronx as he tries to woo Black and Hispanic voters
